Called when tracking the method performance or error.

** Interface Description **

    package aries.runtime;

    public interface IAdapterMethod {
        /**
        * 
        * Tracks the parameter of a method. Used when combining parameters and adding a single value to a profile.
        *
        * @param fullDescriptor Entier method description
        * @param parameterWrapper  Method paramter wrapper class information
        * @return The value of the parameter of the method.
        */
        public String captureParam(String fullDescriptor, Parameter param);

        /**
        *
        * Used when tracking the return value of a method.
        * 
        * @param fullDescriptor Entier method description
        * @param returnValue Method return value
        * @return Returns the return value of the method
        */
        public String captureReturn(String fullDescriptor, Object rtn);

        /**
        *
        * Used when tracking a method error.
        * @param throwable The exception, if an exception occurs during method execution  
        * @return Returns exception messages or profiles to record the event.
        */
        public String catchException(Throwable throwable);
    }

- - -

**Method Description of the main object**

###### ParameterWrapper Description
    public int size() : Return number of paramters
    public Object getThis() : Return an object of the method that collects the parameter
    public Object[] getValues() : Return an array of method paramters
    public Object get(int idx) : Return the parameter of the specified index
    public Parameter getParameter() : Return original Parameter of the object


- - -

** How to configure **

When the class implementing the adapter in the format of jennifer.impl.XXX.jar is placed at the same position as jennifer.jar, the applicable library is automatically recognized without additional settings.
The use of a format such as jennifer.impl.custom-1.0.1.jar enables version control.

    aries.runtime.custom.SampleMethod
    

** Default Implementation **

Contains the default implementation entity which returns a StackTrace for an exception. The following class is an adapter which implements the catchException(Throwable throwable) option.

    aries.runtime.tracer.adapter.MethodAdapterCatchErrorImpl

- - - 

**Sample Implementation**

     public class SampleMethod extends AbstractDefaultAdapter implements IAdapterMethod
    {
        public String captureParameter(String classMethod, ParameterWrapper parameterWrapper)
        {
            return order(classMethod, parameterWrapper);
        }
    
        public String captureReturn(String classMethod, Object returnValue)
        {
            if (returnValue instanceof String)
            {
                return (String) returnValue;
            }

            return (returnValue == null) ? null: returnValue.toString();
        }

        public String catchException(Throwable throwable)
        {
            return null;
        }
    }

